args: ＂I don't even remember what day it is today,\nsuch is the confusion ruling my mind.＂
＂The kingdom I served has suddenly become\nan empire, with him trampling the rest\nof the continent beneath his bootheel.＂
＂He always cared so much for his people;\nwhat could possibly have happened to him?\nI need to meet him and find out.＂
Are we back at the palace now?\n...No, things are too ominous for that.
Oh, we're in the palace—but it belongs to\nthe Dyrenell Empire now. And guess\nwho's sittin' in the big chair?!
Hello, Aurelius. It's me, Cassandra.\nIt has been a while.
Stunned into silence by my youthful\ngood looks? Ah, can't say I blame you.
Still you're not the only one surprised\nby things changing. This palace is\nNOTHING like I remember.
The air is stagnant. Almost...oppressive.\nIt's like I've entered a different world.
I fear I may go mad if I breathe it for too\nmuch longer. Might I open a few windows?
You're a smart, devoted king, Aurelius.\nOne so dedicated to your people that you\nrefused to take even Dragonyule off.
Yet now you expect me to believe you\nsuddenly turned into a murderer who\ndelights in violence?
No, Aurelius. People don't work that way.\nNo one changes into a monster overnight.
I hear you changed after entering\nthe Binding Ruins.
What did you meet there?\nAnd what did you bring BACK?
Whatever it is, it's threatening you.\nWhere in the palace is it?
There's no need to be afraid, Aurelius.\nJust tell me what I need to know,\nand I will set you free.
What malevolent energy... Have you been\ntaken over by something?!
Give it up, kid. None of what you're seeing\nis real.
I cannot stand back and watch this!
Well you're gonna have to, because\nnothing you do can change a memory.
What happened to her after this?
Oh, she got thrown into some dank\ndungeon where she lived on bread\nand rats for a while.
Eventually, she managed to escape and\nmake her way back to the workshop.
That's when she learned that Aurelius had\ndied while she was in the slammer.
＂I couldn't stop thinking that if I hadn't left the\npalace, things might have turned out differently.＂
＂I might have been able to stop him from going\nto the Binding Ruins to begin with.＂
＂I could have gone with him. Protected him.\nMaybe even taken that evil in his place.＂
＂But it was too late. Everything was too late.＂
＂The next thing I knew, I was in one of the\nBinding Ruins. I must have made my way\nthere without even thinking.＂
＂I've no idea why. There was nothing I could\nactually DO there, after all.＂
＂And yet I wandered there, day after day.\nAlmost as if I was...looking for him.＂
＂But he was no longer in this world.\nThere was nothing I could do for him.＂
＂In the end, Cassandra was consumed\nby regret, and spent her days walking\nthe earth like a living corpse.＂ ...The end!
Sure, but it's also the truth. This is a diary,\nsister, not some sappy romance novel\nwhere you're guaranteed a happy ending.
Anyway, there's one more page left.\nWhat do you wanna do?
It coooould be even more depressing than\nall the other stuff you've seen! Muah ha!
I fear to learn what is on that page...
And yet, the Cassandra we know now\nseems much more positive than the one\nin this diary.
If that last page holds the answer to\nthat riddle, I want to see it.
Because I could potentially face a\nsimilar future...
Muah ha... MUAAAAH HA HA HA HA!\nYou're scared, but ya STILL wanna see!
All right, sister! You asked for it!\nLast page, comin' up! ZING!
Oh, we're back in the workshop.\nThere's Cassandra, and over there...\nWait, is that {player_name}?
It's good to see you again, young man.
I came to thank you for what you did\nthe other day. If not for your advice,\nChronos would likely have...
Fiddlesticks! I just gave you a nudge in the\nright direction. But never mind that now.
Are you sure you're all right, young man?\nWhat with your father and your sister?
It hurts. It hurts a lot. But so long as I have\ncountrymen asking for my assistance,\nI have to hold my head up.
You know it's Dragonyule, right?\nNo one would blame you for putting\npaperwork aside and having a bit of fun.
A holiday is no excuse to stop working\nfor my people and country.
You're so earnest—just like he was\nwhen he was younger.
Although I fear you're TOO earnest.\nI can't help but worry that one setback\nmay cause you to keel over and collapse.
If I take a wrong turn, my friends will put\nme right. That's why I can keep fighting.
Ah, yes. It's certainly important to\nhave someone by your side.
And the more allies you have, the better.\nHmm... Yes, that's very true...
＂Today I resolved to join the prince's fight.＂
＂The man I spent so much time with is no more.\nI can do nothing else for him.＂
＂But I can still do for the son what I\ncould not for the father.＂
＂Perhaps this is all just an exercise to make\nmyself feel better...but I can live with that.＂
＂I just don't want any more regrets.＂
So that's what she meant about\nHis Highness being special to her.
But it was only luck that gave her a second\nchance. Not everyone gets that.
So don't you go livin' a life where you\nhold everything back. Don't make the\nsame mistakes she did, yeah?
Remember these memories, grab life by\nthe lapels, and shake it till it pops!
I fear this sudden wave of kindness,\ncoming as it does from you.
Muaaaaah ha ha ha! Welp, storytime\nis over now, sister. I'll see ya around!
